  "time_ut": 1662016125,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db6\u0d82\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dda \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0daf\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Parliament bankrupted the country without knowing it",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "United National Party Member Vajira Abiveardhana said in the Parliament that it is the duty of all the 225 members of the Parliament to demand a proper investigation into the bankruptcy of the country and that the country has been bankrupted without the knowledge of the Parliament.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abewardana said that the country was bankrupted not by the representatives of the parliament but by a group without the knowledge of the parliament, but the blame has been placed on the parliament.",
        "Mr. Abeywardhana said that the Ministry of Finance or the Central Bank does not have the power to bankrupt the country. When they do something they do not have the power to do, everyone remains silent and the representatives of the Parliament are punished.",
        "Mr. Abeywardena said that according to the constitution, there is no power to take arbitrary decisions not to pay the foreign debt and he said that all the 225 people should be ashamed when the power of the parliament was misused.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abeivardhana said that if the situation of the country had been reported to the parliament, the parliament would have met and made a process to deal with it without bankrupting the country.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abewardana said that Parliament has given up financial control and handed it over to others, but by law, financial control belongs to Parliament.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abiveardhana said that there has been a powerless process in Sri Lanka and the President was questioned about it in Parliament when he was a Member of Parliament.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abiveardhana said that the 225 responsibility of the Parliament is not necessary to bankrupt the country and those who have declared the country bankrupt have done illegal work if the Parliament has not approved this process.",
        "Mr. Vajira Abeywardena said this while participating in the budget debate in Parliament."
      ],
